**Explanation:** The integral \( G(s) = \int_0^\infty e^{-st} \, dt \) converges to \( \frac{1}{s} \) when \( \text{Re}\{s\} > 0 \) and diverges otherwise. The Laplace transform of \( f(t) = 1 \) is indeed \( \mathcal{L}\{1\} = \frac{1}{s} \) for \( \text{Re}\{s\} > 0 \).
